  "prompt": "What is meant by internships?",
  "response": "An internship is a temporary work experience, usually undertaken by students or recent graduates, to gain practical skills and experience in a specific field or industry. It can be either paid or unpaid, and the duration can range from a few weeks to several months. Internships provide opportunities to apply academic knowledge in real-world settings, build professional networks, and enhance one's resume. They are common in various fields such as business, engineering, healthcare, and the arts.",
